cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with the segmentation of brain tumors in MRI data using computerized methods. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The methods used involve graph-based optimization and balloon inflation forces, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG, cs.NE). The paper also involves the evaluation of the segmentation results using a similarity coefficient, which is a common metric used in multimedia (cs.MM).
